    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by heightened operational readiness and strategic prioritization of key regional contingencies. The most critical development is the deployment of USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) to the Arabian Sea via the Atlantic, bypassing the Mediterranean, which underscores a deliberate strategic pivot toward countering Iranian aggression in the Strait of Hormuz. This naval deployment is supported by two destroyers—USS Frank E. Petersen (DDG-121) and USS Michael Murphy (DDG-112)—conducting escort missions for merchant vessels through the Strait, directly responding to recent U.S. strikes on suspected narco boats in the Eastern Pacific and ongoing mine clearance operations in the Strait of Hormuz. The multi-domain response includes sustained logistics and intelligence support from high-altitude strategic airlifters (C-17, C-5M) and ISR platforms (Beechcraft 200) operating on transcontinental routes, indicating a robust overseas contingency framework. Training operations remain active across multiple regions, with advanced pilot training (T-6, T-38) concentrated in the central and southeastern U.S., while specialized platforms like the V-22 Osprey and HH-60 Pave Hawks conduct regional security and search-and-rescue missions. The Coast Guard’s HH-60 Jayhawk off California and Navy MH-60 Seahawks near Norfolk reflect a comprehensive maritime security posture. Notably, the absence of major surface combatant deployments in the Pacific, despite regional tensions, suggests a deliberate prioritization of Middle Eastern contingencies, though this could shift rapidly if Indo-Pacific stability deteriorates. The overall assessment indicates a U.S. military maintaining high operational tempo, rapid deployment readiness, and a focus on countering hybrid threats in critical chokepoints, with a clear emphasis on maritime security and asymmetric warfare responses.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
